   <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_dpc.xml" xtrc="title:1;13:26">Downstream Port Containment</title>
   <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_dpc.xml" xtrc="body:1;16:32">
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_dpc.xml" xtrc="p:1;19:29">Downstream Port Containment (DPC) is a Downstream (DS) Port function and is a PCI-SIG Base Specification 4.0 feature. DPC is an error containment mechanism for Downstream Ports (DSP) and provides an automatic disabling of the Link below a DSP following an unmasked uncorrectable error. It <ph status="deleted" rev="deltaxml-delete" class="- topic/ph " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_dpc.xml" xtrc="ph:1;19:361">disable</ph>
         <ph status="new" rev="deltaxml-add" class="- topic/ph " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_dpc.xml" xtrc="ph:2;20:46">disables</ph> the port <ph status="deleted" rev="deltaxml-delete" class="- topic/ph " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_dpc.xml" xtrc="ph:3;20:112">to shut down </ph>and silently drops all subsequent TLPs from the DSP. This prevents the potential spread of data corruption and enables error recovery as supported by the host software.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_dpc.xml" xtrc="p:2;24:29">DPC is supported as a combination of hardware and firmware. The hardware handles detection while the firmware manages the port containment interrupt/message handling.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_dpc.xml" xtrc="p:3;28:29">The benefits of DPC are to provide customers with more robust error containment and an opportunity for error recovery. DPC improves PCIe error containment and allows software to recover from asynchronous removal events that are not possible with previous solutions.</p>
      <note audience="MSCCInternal" class="- topic/note " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_dpc.xml" xtrc="note:1;33:32">
