         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_dpc.xml" xtrc="p:6;65:24">DPC can be manually enabled by writing the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_dpc.xml" xtrc="i:1;67:27">DPC Trigger Enable</i> bit in the DPC Control Register of all relevant DSPs via the configuration file patch table. See <xref href="https://kb.microsemi.com/display/SDS/%5BHow-To%5D+-+Manually+Enable+DPC+Support+in+Switchtec" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_dpc.xml" xtrc="xref:1;71:34"><?ditaot gentext?>https://kb.microsemi.com/display/SDS/%5BHow-To%5D+-+Manually+Enable+DPC+Support+in+Switchtec</xref> for more details.</p>
