      <section class="- topic/section " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_dpc.xml" xtrc="section:2;76:35">
         <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_dpc.xml" xtrc="title:4;79:32">Switchtec DPC Auto-clear</title>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_dpc.xml" xtrc="p:7;82:24">Switchtec features a DPC trigger auto-clear mechanism which enables DPC support in systems that do not natively support drivers that can clear the DPC trigger. In these cases, the Switchtec DPC auto-clear feature can automatically clear and re-arm the DPC hardware after a fixed timeout value. </p>
